At this stage it's better to have docs, at least for non-Prop fields.
Fixed! Let me know if the description sounds reasonable, I am not an expert in bicategories.
This is a perfectly good reaction from the `simpNF` linter. The main reason is that there is no composition in the LHS. We may remove this comment;
Okay, I will remove it from `Oplax.lean` then as well!

```suggestion
attribute [simp, reassoc] map₂_leftUnitor map₂_rightUnitor
```
Made corresponding change to `Oplax.lean` and `Pseudofunctor.lean`

```suggestion
      F.map f ◁ F.mapComp g h ≫ F.mapComp f (g ≫ h) ≫ F.map₂ (α_ f g h).inv := by
```

```suggestion
      (α_ (F.map f) (F.map g) (F.map h)).inv ≫ F.mapComp f g ▷ F.map h ≫
        F.mapComp (f ≫ g) h ≫ F.map₂ (α_ f g h).hom := by
```

```suggestion
def mkOfLax (F : LaxFunctor B C) (F' : F.PseudoCore) : Pseudofunctor B C where
```
